Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.21,0:00:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stars are marginally fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.78,0:00:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They can represent culprits or celebrities!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.60,0:00:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's stage is a television network.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.18,0:00:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The passion of a drama quickly results in a case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.74,0:00:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.29,0:00:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.13,0:00:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.21,0:00:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we felt the same light the moment we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots and lots of the same emotions filled our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the signals you sent destroyed my theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These feelings were always beyond your reach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, let's fight, go against our morals...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And aim for a wider world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.15,0:01:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this town changes someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.10,0:01:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.35,0:01:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, a drama scriptwriter has requested\Nthe presence of me, Mouri Kogorou?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.61,0:01:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we all want to hear Detective Mouri's opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.10,0:01:59.29,CharCards01 bord,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)} Inoue Ryouko (40)\N{\fs13} Nichuri Tv Film Department Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.72,0:01:59.49,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Have you seen the show "Detective Megure" before?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.53,0:02:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a detective drama, right?\NI may have seen it a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.83,0:02:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watch it every week!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.91,0:02:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.41,0:02:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are three people who take\Nturns writing the drama's script.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.50,0:02:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been on air for five years now...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.09,0:02:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we're almost out of ideas for motives and tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.09,0:02:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, I presume you would like to delve into\Nthe past cases of one Mouri Kogorou?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.10,0:02:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Magure's such a great show, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.27,0:02:32.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not every episode is great, but every once in\Na while the deductions will blow you away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.15,0:02:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For instance...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.48,0:02:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Secret Chamber No. 52," the trick was unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.78,0:02:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Magure{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, that chamber is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.07,0:02:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was something that was only\Nconstructed later, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.12,0:02:48.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using a crane to lift up the entire house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.21,0:02:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would've guessed that\Nsuch a large-scale trick was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.00,0:03:00.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, even that didn't escape the\Neyes of yours truly, Magure Rintarou.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.57,0:03:08.53,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(900,0)} Episode 99 [Secret Chamber No. 52] Final
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.26,0:03:08.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really outdid yourselves with the trick that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really enjoyed watching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.69,0:03:17.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I agree, Secret Chamber No. 52" was\Nproduced quite well for a mystery, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.44,0:03:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That aired at least two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.15,0:03:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, how old are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.95,0:03:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched it on video a while ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.20,0:03:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's how it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.42,0:03:33.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was close...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.17,0:03:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.50,0:03:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allow me to tell your drama script\Nwriters about every case I've solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, can I go too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.59,0:03:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really want to see who writes the\Nscripts for Detective Magure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.68,0:03:52.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Half Completed Crime Mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.74,0:04:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did we come too early?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.11,0:04:07.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We still have an hour left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.45,0:04:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a cafe on the top floor, I think
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.66,0:04:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Yagami, a scriptwriter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.58,0:04:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who oversees the production of\N"Detective Magure," asked me to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.58,0:04:17.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, please wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person is one of the drama's\Nthree scriptwriters, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.34,0:04:26.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He looks like an arrogant fatso to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.82,0:04:28.05,CharCards02 bord,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)} Yagami Jouji (50)\N{\fs16} Scriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.06,0:04:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, it's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.88,0:04:37.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My taxi got stuck in traffic jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.71,0:04:37.70,CharCards03 bord,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)} Kouda Morio (29)\N{\fs16} Scriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the first time in half a year\Nthat the three of you got together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.78,0:04:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, before Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} comes, please\Ndiscuss the direction of the series.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.04,0:04:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like something drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.29,0:04:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.42,0:04:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, I'm not thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.00,0:04:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll get some drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.75,0:05:00.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you guys like?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.00,0:05:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coffee... hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.38,0:05:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.09,0:05:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it, I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.77,0:05:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to trouble you like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.23,0:05:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can leave that to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.23,0:05:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's like some kind of servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.82,0:05:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't discussing the drama more\Nimportant than getting the drinks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to think someone like him can\Nbe considered a drama scriptwriter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.24,0:05:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't his scripts been fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.99,0:05:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not talking about his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.66,0:05:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about the way he acts\Non a regular basis, Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.08,0:05:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he's still new, it's normal for him\Nto have a lot of things to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.79,0:05:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just fire him already, Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.80,0:05:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We only need Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and\NI to work on Detective Magure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.18,0:05:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.60,0:05:53.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry for making you wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.81,0:05:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.94,0:06:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to add milk, right, Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.44,0:06:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.69,0:06:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.49,0:06:12.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly, if that klutz isn't dropping\Nsomething, he's forgetting something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.19,0:06:18.09,CharCards04 bord,,0,0,0,,{\fade(300,0)} Sakuma Akira (45)\N{\fs16} Scriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.67,0:06:16.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's still young, and isn't used to everything yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.35,0:06:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:43.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.78,0:06:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.08,0:06:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.33,0:06:56.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.70,0:06:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The address is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.42,0:07:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.88,0:07:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The smell of almonds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.51,0:07:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death is potassium cyanide poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.39,0:07:23.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Four people...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:25.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And four drinks, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.99,0:07:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cup on the floor is poisoned, as expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.00,0:07:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But none of the other three cups are\Nshowing traces of the substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.88,0:07:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the culprit only\Npoisoned Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.71,0:07:49.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's pretty much it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.09,0:07:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who prepared the drinks\Nwas you, Kouda Morio{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.84,0:07:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked what they wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:07:59.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone wanted hot coffee, but I had Japanese tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.43,0:08:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But aren't the drinks normally prepared by\Nsomeone who works at the TV station?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.27,0:08:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, they are, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.48,0:08:10.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just started my scriptwriting career.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.99,0:08:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm trying my best to help everyone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.20,0:08:15.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not strange, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.62,0:08:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's so strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.49,0:08:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.79,0:08:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone placed the poison in a random cup...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it just happened to be served to Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.21,0:08:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that this was an indiscriminate murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.80,0:08:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't think of anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:41.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're saying that Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} refused your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.02,0:08:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he could do it himself, and didn't need any help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.35,0:08:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.98,0:08:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, can you come with us for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.49,0:08:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After some investigation, the only person who\Ncould have placed the poison was Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.50,0:09:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suggesting that someone committed indiscriminate\Nmurder was pretty much his last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only he could be the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.59,0:09:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we still don't know his motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.88,0:09:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.80,0:09:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you to stay in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.39,0:09:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't they all co-workers working together on a drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.60,0:09:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they poison someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.68,0:09:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that they're co-workers...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.48,0:09:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell us everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.11,0:09:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.94,0:09:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took turns\Nwriting the scripts for Detective Magure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.45,0:09:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some time later, a self-proclaimed loyal fan of\Nthe show sent us one of his own drama scripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.50,0:09:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person was the newcomer, Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.50,0:09:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After reading his work, I thought it was pretty interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I let him on board as the drama's third scriptwriter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.92,0:09:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} thought highly of his work, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.88,0:10:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason, Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} absolutely hated him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.85,0:10:02.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.93,0:10:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told me to fire him on several occasions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.31,0:10:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.81,0:10:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think he probably had an idea of what was going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.40,0:10:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've been hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.69,0:10:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.19,0:10:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll do whatever I can to write more for this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.16,0:10:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really want to make a name for\Nmyself as a drama scriptwriter!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.79,0:10:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} gambled his whole\Nfuture on Detective Magure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.92,0:10:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did everything he could to get him fired.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.72,0:10:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's obvious, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.30,0:10:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has to be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.05,0:10:45.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We have the motive now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.90,0:11:01.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But... if he's the one that did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.08,0:11:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.70,0:11:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already know who the culprit is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.00,0:11:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you don't have any evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there are still things that haven't been cleared up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.71,0:11:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up and leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the famous detective Mouri Kogorou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.22,0:11:23.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is that really all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.55,0:11:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think that... I killed Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be true that I didn't get along with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.44,0:11:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.73,0:11:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I had put poison in the coffee, how\Nwould I get Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to drink it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.61,0:11:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of the three cups, only one had poison in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.91,0:11:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, when I was getting the milk,\NI wasn't at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.75,0:11:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that I didn't give him\Nthe cup; he took it himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.00,0:12:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have predicted which cup he would take.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.38,0:12:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.72,0:12:04.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's exactly the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.59,0:12:07.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If this person is the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.60,0:12:11.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How did he get Yagami{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} to choose\Nthe cup with the poison in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.98,0:12:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.36,0:12:20.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brought in the cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.90,0:12:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you gave Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} the cup with no poison in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.78,0:12:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only two cups remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.24,0:12:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both cups are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.12,0:12:30.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would I know which cup Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would pick?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.37,0:12:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's easy-first, you arranged the cups like so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.50,0:12:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, in that room, Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nseat would have been over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.50,0:12:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course he would take the cup closest to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.01,0:12:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s junior,\Nso it's not like he would just reach for a cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.18,0:12:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.81,0:12:51.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is that really what he did?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.06,0:12:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, even though we're each other's senior and\Njunior, we're already familiar with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.81,0:13:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, I was definitely the first one to take\Na cup, and passed the last one to Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.57,0:13:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, wouldn't I be suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.49,0:13:12.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you really are quite suspicious of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.08,0:13:17.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell me the trick that I used to get\NYagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to drink the poisoned coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.71,0:13:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Solve that mystery first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:22.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Such an aggressive look in his eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.30,0:13:25.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He's definitely the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.84,0:13:29.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yet he has so much confidence in his trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.39,0:13:32.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two people and two drinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.31,0:13:35.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a 50% chance for someone to choose either cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.19,0:13:40.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What exactly did he do to get a probability of 100%?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.24,0:13:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be honest, my suspicions of Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} are a bit shaky.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.24,0:13:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if the person he wanted\Nto kill was really Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.75,0:13:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took that cup of coffee...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.79,0:14:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would have stopped him no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.05,0:14:06.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he said he forgot to bring the milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.59,0:14:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he were the culprit, would he have\Nleft the scene of the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.01,0:14:10.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.43,0:14:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't he think it through that\Nsomething like this could happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.43,0:14:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.43,0:14:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you listening, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.57,0:14:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's going to happen to Detective Magure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.61,0:14:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't be canceled, will it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.70,0:14:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.78,0:14:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for something like this to happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.66,0:14:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We worked hard to get to where we are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that the Detective Magure episode list?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.42,0:14:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I see?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.21,0:14:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.38,0:14:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.89,0:14:53.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.01,0:14:56.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one was written by Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.39,0:14:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,[Secret Chamber No. 52.]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.52,0:15:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You also said that it was worth watching, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.90,0:15:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, that one was Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s first drama script.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.45,0:15:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a newcomer that skilled to join us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.28,0:15:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even I was amazed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.41,0:15:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,[The Club of Supporting Actors]\Nwas also written by Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.79,0:15:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.21,0:15:23.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Does this mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.83,0:15:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most of the scripts were written by\NYagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.80,0:15:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because the two of\Nthem were the main writers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.30,0:15:34.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means that anyone else who was\Ntalented wouldn't have the chance to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how the motive for this murder came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.39,0:15:39.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}With that, every riddle is now solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:42.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.10,0:15:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.19,0:15:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've finally solved this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.98,0:15:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We finally saw through the culprit's trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.69,0:15:51.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, there were two people and two cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.62,0:16:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After thinking about it, getting the\Nvictim to choose the right cup...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.00,0:16:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could be accomplished using only one method.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.50,0:16:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.09,0:16:13.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To pray for a miracle to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.26,0:16:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, was that supposed\Nto be your great explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.31,0:16:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, I kid you not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.19,0:16:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The success rate was 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.15,0:16:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a chance of failure, but\NKouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took that chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.44,0:16:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could you be satisfied after\Nbeing driven away like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.78,0:16:37.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were so desperate and determined that,\Nin the end, you did something this shocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.62,0:16:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.12,0:16:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Inspector, I'm absolutely sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.80,0:16:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.21,0:16:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be the legendary...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.67,0:16:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sleeping Kogorou?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.93,0:16:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying I took such a drastic risk?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.60,0:17:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.64,0:17:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really did consider it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.23,0:17:05.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.52,0:17:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hear me out, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.19,0:17:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.36,0:17:11.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said earlier that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.90,0:17:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should first discover how you made Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Ndrink the poisoned cup of coffee, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there's no way of finding out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.49,0:17:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I say this because you never used a trick to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.58,0:17:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't use a trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.08,0:17:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, he didn't use one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.09,0:17:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how did he get Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nto drink the poisoned coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.59,0:17:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we get to that, allow me to\Nfirst explain how it all happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:42.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan, bring it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.72,0:17:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.60,0:17:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was what Conan borrowed earlier\Nthe list of Detective Magure episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.90,0:17:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing this, I was amazed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:18:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the Magure drama, there would be a mystery\Nwith an amazing deduction every few episodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.62,0:18:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would have a unique trick, and yet remain logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.83,0:18:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And most importantly, it would\Nalways keep the spirit of fair play.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.79,0:18:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Secret Chamber No. 52," for example, was like that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.29,0:18:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same with "The Club of Supporting Actors"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.30,0:18:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Massacre at the Empty Well"...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.30,0:18:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "When the Green Door Opened."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.05,0:18:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are all...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.51,0:18:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right-scripts that I happen to admire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.60,0:18:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you wrote them, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.90,0:18:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After discovering this...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.23,0:18:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I began to think back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.57,0:18:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, who could write such perfect mysteries...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.78,0:18:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would never gamble on a 50% outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.41,0:18:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, I noticed something you\Nhad done that raised my suspicions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.58,0:18:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, why did you leave the scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.00,0:18:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgetting the milk must have been\Nsomething you planned beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.47,0:19:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not caring about which coffee each of them chose...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.64,0:19:07.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably wanted to stress this point, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.68,0:19:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it would have still been suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.89,0:19:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure said this earlier:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.69,0:19:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if the person he wanted\Nto kill was really Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.61,0:19:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took that cup of coffee...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.49,0:19:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would have stopped him no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.78,0:19:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter what fancy method you used since\Nsomething this unpredictable could still happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.08,0:19:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, who could write such seamless deductions,\Nwould never fail to consider such a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.67,0:19:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In spite of this, you left the conference room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.21,0:19:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.92,0:19:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.38,0:19:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether or not you killed Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.52,0:19:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.93,0:19:51.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.94,0:19:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter whether it was\NYagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Saguma{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.82,0:20:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he didn't need any sort of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.69,0:20:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're saying, he would be satisfied as\Nlong as Yagami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or I was killed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.41,0:20:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's quite a haphazard way of committing a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.79,0:20:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, this wasn't done haphazardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.71,0:20:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter who was killed, there would only be one result.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.42,0:20:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As long as one of the two main writers was eliminated...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.76,0:20:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chances for Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the third writer, to\Nprove himself would have greatly increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.38,0:20:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doing whatever you could to write\Nmore for Detective Magure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.60,0:20:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the real motive for the whole\Nincident, wasn't it, Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.06,0:20:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.40,0:20:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll do whatever I can to write more for this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.86,0:20:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really want to make a name for\Nmyself as a drama scriptwriter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.91,0:20:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.16,0:20:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This incident may seem to have\Nonly a 50% chance of succeeding...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.21,0:20:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as long as one of the two drank the\Npoisoned coffee, he would have been in luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.29,0:21:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why his method of committing the crime\Nhad, in fact, a 100% chance of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.71,0:21:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.68,0:21:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm already 29...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Become a prominent drama scriptwriter.\NBefore turning 30, I wanted to...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.11,0:21:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.41,0:21:33.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What does it matter if you're prominent...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.16,0:21:36.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Or if you're only writing one out of every ten episodes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.87,0:21:38.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Those who love your work will watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.38,0:21:41.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Inoue{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} is also a fan of your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.00,0:21:44.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I remember what you've done. Everyone does.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.18,0:21:47.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Every one of your episodes blew me away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.64,0:21:51.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You were really foolish...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.18,0:22:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop the world and smile gently...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.36,0:22:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to be closer to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.24,0:22:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've fallen for you time and time again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.62,0:22:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My tears overflow as the dawn approaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.08,0:22:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The warmth you give me makes me forget to take a breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.05,0:22:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm afraid of losing the feeling of your fingertips stroking my hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.23,0:22:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The attraction that pulls us together...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.36,0:22:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we be separated tomorrow, I would search for you to no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.54,0:23:01.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop the world and smile gently...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.79,0:23:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I will always be by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.38,0:23:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let the light of dawn shine upon you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.93,0:23:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And envelop the two us of like this forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.19,0:23:24.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Detective Magure's still canceled?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.11,0:23:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Detective Magure" finished,\N"New Detective Magure" starting soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.90,0:23:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hear the main character underwent a name change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.53,0:23:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Magure Rintarou became Magure Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.58,0:23:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Magure Kogo...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.25,0:23:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it sounds a lot like Fluky Kogorou."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.79,0:23:43.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Isn't that you exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.05,0:23:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking at you, one would think you just\NDeducted something unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.42,0:23:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuburaya Mitsuhiko. This is a failure of a lifetime!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.24,0:24:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should tell Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} about something like this.\NIf we don't make it... What will we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.61,0:24:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,-Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!\N-Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.34,0:24:09.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's try the back too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.76,0:24:11.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.33,0:24:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Detective Group Chasing The blue Bird
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.84,0:24:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.93,0:24:20.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soy sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.14,0:24:22.07,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next week is 'Aoitori.'
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.09,0:24:23.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What? Aodori?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.14,0:24:24.43,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No, Inspector Mogure
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.46,0:24:25.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Megure.
